-- China Legislator Calls for Restraint in Korean Peninsula, Xinhua Reports
-- B y   B l o o m b e r g   N e w s
-- 2010-11-24T02:27:00Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-11-24/china-legislator-calls-for-restraint-in-korean-peninsula-xinhua-reports.html
Restraint is required on the Korean
Peninsula to ease tensions, Xinhua News Agency cited Zha Peixin,
vice chairman of the Foreign Affairs Committee of the Chinese
National People’s Congress, as saying.  “People do recognize the six-party talks are really the
best way to address this issue,” Zha said, according to the
report.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
